Storage and transfer of your information
6.
What security measures do we take to safeguard your information?
7.
Updates to Privacy Policy
8.
How to contact us
1. What information may be collected during your use of the App?
a. "
Personal Information
" is information about an individual that can be used to personally identify that individual. Examples of Personal Information include: name, address, unique device identifier, unique friend code (Friend Code), date of birth, telephone number, fax number, email address, and video/photo of an individual. Personal Information can also include Non-Personal Information that, when combined with other information, can be used to identify an individual. Some of the technical information that is automatically collected from your mobile device also falls under the category of Personal Information. This includes your unique device identifier ("UDID" or "device ID"), IP address, and identifiers for advertisers.
b. "
Non-Personal Information
" is information about an individual that, by itself, does not identify that individual. Some examples of Non-Personal Information include your anonymous client ID and in-game nickname, demographic information (age, gender, etc.), device hardware and software data, broad geographic information, App usage statistics, and purchase history.
c. "
Financial Information
" is information relating to payments and billing (e.g. account information, billing address, payment processing data). We do not collect Financial Information from you unless you voluntarily provide it - which we encourage you not to do. All financial transactions that may occur within the App are facilitated by a third party payment service (such as Apple or Google). Please review the Apple and Google Wallet privacy policies to learn more about how our third-party payment processors handle your Personal Information and Financial Information.
Back to top
2. How do we collect information?
We may receive Personal Information and Non-Personal Information from you directly when you voluntarily give it to us as part of a customer support inquiry or when you access certain features or functions in the App that require personal information, such as when you connect and share to a social network through the App. Through some social networking websites' privacy settings, you can control what data you share. For more information about how Facebook handles your Personal Information, please refer to their privacy policy and terms of use.
We also receive Non-Personal Information directly from you when you create a nickname, transfer password or make in-App purchases. You may be able to create a nickname within the App. When creating a nickname, please do not use your actual name, initials, or any other information that could be used to personally identify you.
We also passively collect Non-Personal information about you through technological means like cookies, web beacons, Apple ID, identifiers for advertisers, IP address, log files, analytics software embedded in the App, and other software tools. We may also receive information about you from social networks you connect to through the App, our third-party service providers, or other sources, such as Google or Apple in relation to in-App purchase statistics.
See Google's general privacy policy here:
http://www.google.com/policies/privacy/
;
Google’s privacy policy here:
https://wallet.google.com/legaldocument?family=0.privacynotice&hl=en
;
Apple's privacy policy here:
https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/en-ww/
and Facebook's privacy policies here:
https://www.facebook.com/about/privacy/
.
Back to top
3. How do we use information we collect about you?
We use Personal Information to provide certain features within the App, such as social network integration, customized push notifications, to respond to customer inquiries, to generate and track Friend Code, as well as to provide customer support, for internal business operations, and for identity verification purposes.
We may use Non-Personal Information to monitor system performance and internal business operations, to send push notifications, to improve the App, to fulfill requests for additional products, services, and marketing activities, to provide customer support, and to conduct research.
Whatever the purpose may be, we will only collect information to the extent reasonably necessary to fulfill your requests and our legitimate business objectives.
Back to top
4. When will we disclose your information?
We may share information with outside entities that assist with internal operations (including, without limitation, technical support, push notifications, ad serving, hosting, data storage, analytics, and customer support). These entities shall include third parties located in foreign countries. In the course of providing such services, these companies may have access to your Personal Information and Non-Personal Information. These entities have agreed to maintain the confidentiality and security of all the Personal Information they obtain from us.
We may also share information with social networks that you consent to connect to the App. These social networks may have access to your Personal Information and Non-Personal Information.
We do not sell or rent Personal Information to third parties. Additionally, we will not allow third parties to use information about you for their own marketing purposes or the marketing purposes of other unaffiliated third parties without your prior consent. We may share aggregated, Non-Personal Information publicly and with our partners.
We will also disclose information when we believe in good faith that such disclosures (a) are required by law, including, for example, to comply with a court order or subpoena, or (b) will help to enforce our Terms; protect your safety or security, including the safety and security of property that belongs to you; and/or, protect the safety and security of the App or third parties.
In the event of a merger, sale of assets, acquisition, dissolution, reorganization, bankruptcy, change of control or other similar event, your Personal Information may be transferred to our successor or assign, if permitted by and done in accordance with applicable law, or if we sell one or more of our businesses, your Personal Information may be transferred as a part of the sale.
Back to top
5. Storage and transfer of your information
The information we collect from you will be stored predominantly in Ireland, Japan, and the United States.  You acknowledge that your information may be transferred outside of your home territory to Ireland, the United States and/or Japan and you consent to this transfer by using the App.  You also acknowledge that the applicable laws of the territory in which we store your information may not afford the same level of protection as those in your country of residence..
Back to top
6. What security measures do we take to safeguard your information?
No security measure is perfect or impenetrable, but we take commercially reasonable measures to protect information that we receive and have implemented technical, administrative, and physical security measures to protect your Personal Information from unauthorized access and improper use. We will continue to examine our internal policies as needed, and will improve as appropriate.
Back to top
7. Updates to Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post any changes here with an updated date, and, if there are any material changes in the way we collect, use, or share Personal Information, we will notify you by prominently posting notice with the updated version of the App.
Back to top
8. How to contact us
In order to request information about this Privacy Policy, review your Personal Information, or to file a complaint, please email us using the form below.
Help Desk: The Pokémon Company Personal Information
Help Desk
You may also contact us at:
The Pokémon Company International, Inc.
